  "text": "In order to visualize whether or not Kp-10 stimulates motility of breast cancer cells in real-time, we performed scratch assays as described [CITATION_1] . We observed that Kp-10 treatments (10 nM or 100 nM) significantly enhance the distance travelled by the MDA-MB-231 cells over time, when compared to cells seeded only in Figure 3 . Kp-10 stimulates breast cancer cell motility. Treatment with both 10 nM and 100 nM Kp-10 enhances distance closed by MDA-MB-231 cells in a scratch assay. Scale bar, 100 mm. a, P,0.05 for 10 nM Kp-10 when compared to untreated control cells seeded in serum; b, P,0.05 for 100 nM Kp-10 when compared to untreated control cells seeded in serum. Bars represent mean distance travelled in mm 6 SEM. Data from five independent experiments. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0021599.g003 10% serum (Fig. 3) . Taken together, these results suggest that Kp-10 stimulates not only breast cancer cell invasion, but also enhances their motility.",
